HEADWORD: Urceolate
<hw>Ur"ce*o*late</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>urceolus</ets>, dim. of <ets>urceus</ets> a pitcher or
waterpot.]</ety> <fld>(Nat. Hist.)</fld> <def>Shaped like a pitcher or
urn; swelling below, and contracted at the orifice, as a calyx or
corolla.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

